profile:
Creative Home Furnishings is a furniture store in Vancouver, located in the Armoury District. We specialize in custom furniture, condo furniture, and solid wood furniture, including built to order furniture, most locally made.

Our focus is on clean and sleek designs with a clear focus on the modern home, condo or apartment. You can personalize your choices of stain colour, hardware, fabrics and more.

We carry:

    Living Room furniture
    Bedroom Furniture
    Dining Room Furniture
    Lighting
    Tables
    Dining Room Tables
    Dining Stools
    Curio Cabinets
    Sofas
    Beds
    Nightstands
    TV Stands
    Bookcases
    Desks
    Much More

We ship and deliver to fine homes and condos throughout North America.

History

Creative Home Furnishings was established in 1989. We have two stores, one in Coquitlam and our Vancouver store. Our furniture stores sell custom made furniture, most solid wood. We even carry furniture in sizes perfect for condos and apartments.

Our focus is on locally-made furniture which can be fully customized to meet your needs. This location has a little bit of everything: bedroom, dining, occasionals, sofas and lighting. It is also the main display space for our Koncept Lighting.

We provide a very high level of customer service. Our staff has a passion for design and we are able to provide in-house consultations to assist you in creating your perfect home. Whether you need guidance with choosing colour palettes, appropriate sized pieces for your space and lifestyle, or a sounding board for your style decisions, we are here for you. Our service even extends to designing custom pieces which can meet your unique needs, such as stereo cabinets to fit your components, or a buffet to fit an alcove.

About The Owners

Maria and Blair own Creative Home Furnishings and they have a passion for great design. They have an education in engineering and architecture, and have renovated and designed homes and a bed and breakfast. While building the new home, they were able to incorporate the wood that was cleared from the lot into the design features of the home. This experience inspired them to take on a larger enterprise where creativity is key.

Maria and Blair purchased Creative Home Furnishings in 2007. They saw the store as an opportunity to meld their passion for great design with their love of locally built product. In a world where so much of what we buy is mass produced, we offer something that is made with care. The collections are the l results of this quest: the clean designs, strong lines and solid construction evoke the vernacular of the westcoast, and the cultures which have influenced it.
